author: Scott Prather
title: Saints Thursday Injury Report, Week 5
text:
Saints Thursday Injury Report, Week 5 By Scott Prather October 8, 2015 5:07 PM Share on Twitter Drew Brees talks to Terron Armstead 
New Orleans Saints quarterback Drew Brees is no longer on the teamâ€™s injury report, but several players still are as the team prepares for their week 5 matchup at Philadelphia on Sunday against the Eagles. 
Left tackle Terron Armstead (knee), punter Thomas Morstead (right quadricep) and Tim Lelito (back) all missed practice today. 
Safety Jairus Byrd (knee), guard Jahri Evans (knee) and cornerback Keenan Lewis (hip) were limited. 
Wide reciever Marques Colston and defensive tackle Kevin Williams were both back at pratice Thursday after sitting out Wednesday for rest. 
Wide receiver Brandin Cooks (ankle) was a full participant. 
Kickoff Sunday in Philadelphia is set for noon.
